# Project Structure Guide

The main entry point is [main.py](mdc:main.py), which starts the MCP server and handles CLI commands.

Core logic is in [src/ast_grep_mcp/](mdc:src/ast_grep_mcp):
- [ast_analyzer.py](mdc:src/ast_grep_mcp/ast_analyzer.py): Core AST analysis functionality
- [server.py](mdc:src/ast_grep_mcp/server.py): MCP server implementation
- [language_handlers/](mdc:src/ast_grep_mcp/language_handlers): Language-specific modules

Language handlers are in [src/ast_grep_mcp/language_handlers/](mdc:src/ast_grep_mcp/language_handlers):
- [python_handler.py](mdc:src/ast_grep_mcp/language_handlers/python_handler.py): Python support
- [javascript_handler.py](mdc:src/ast_grep_mcp/language_handlers/javascript_handler.py): JavaScript support
- [base.py](mdc:src/ast_grep_mcp/language_handlers/base.py): Base handler class
- [__init__.py](mdc:src/ast_grep_mcp/language_handlers/__init__.py): Registers handlers

Project configuration is in [pyproject.toml](mdc:pyproject.toml).

See [README.md](mdc:README.md) for usage, development, and more details.
